fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
A monoidal category  C consists of the following data:

an underlying category  C;

a bifunctor  C\times  C\xrightarrow {\otimes } C, called the
      monoidal product;

an object I\in  C, called the monoidal unit;

a natural isomorphism (x\otimes  y)\otimes  z\xrightarrow {\alpha _{x,y,z}}       x\otimes (y\otimes  z), called the associator;

a natural isomorphism I\otimes  x\xrightarrow {\lambda _x} x, called the
      left unitor;

a natural isomorphism x\otimes  I\xrightarrow {\rho _x} x, called the
      right unitor.

  This data must make the following coherence conditions, called the
  triangle and pentagon identities, commute:





    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
  \usetikzlibrary{shapes.geometric}
  \usetikzlibrary{calc}
  \usetikzlibrary{matrix}
  \usetikzlibrary{decorations.markings}

  \tikzset{
    % basics
    square/.style={draw, regular polygon, regular polygon sides=4},
    triangle/.style={draw, regular polygon, regular polygon sides=3},
  }

  \tikzset{
    % string diagrams
    state/.style={triangle, shape border rotate=180, anchor=north},
    costate/.style={triangle, anchor=south},
    morphism/.style={draw, rectangle},
    over/.style={
      draw=white,
      double=black,
      % default is .4pt
      line width=1.2pt,
      double distance=.4pt,
      text=black
    },
  }

  \tikzset{ 
